{"sequence":35,"timestamp":"2026-04-17T19:45:09.311376666Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-adcef5e2","body":"finding_summary: `build_e2e_milestone_scenario_fixture()` first materializes a placeholder milestone and then rematerializes the real scenario bundle on top of it. `src/test_support/e2e_fixtures.rs:67` creates the seed milestone with `MilestoneFixtureBuilder::new(...).add_bead(...)`, `src/test_support/e2e_fixtures.rs:80` writes a different bundle with new bead IDs, and `src/test_support/e2e_fixtures.rs:91` returns the journal/task-run state reloaded from disk. Because `MilestoneFixtureBuilder::write_into()` already persists a full plan and journal (`src/test_support/fixtures.rs:585`, `src/test_support/fixtures.rs:615`, `src/test_support/fixtures.rs:698`), the returned fixture carries stale history for the seed `ms-e2e-scenario.bead-*` plan before the advertised scenario plan. That makes the fixture semantically wrong for later e2e coverage that inspects milestone history or lifecycle transitions.\naffected_files:\n- src/test_support/e2e_fixtures.rs\n- src/test_support/fixtures.rs\nremediation_hint: Build the workspace without pre-seeding a milestone, or add a builder path that initializes the workspace and materializes the scenario bundle exactly once so the journal and persisted history only describe the real scenario.","dedup_key":"baaedec18ee599224717b64e81e404266d6abf51c89ee76a4be5557f6966e5c4","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260417184955","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
